# The SPA shell and PWA update-check files must never be cached by the
# browser or any CDN in front of it — otherwise a user's browser can keep
# running a stale service worker after a deploy, which then 404s fetching
# JS chunks whose content-hashed filenames changed in the new build,
# breaking the app until that cache naturally expires (observed as
# "the site doesn't work" for some users but not others).
<IfModule mod_headers.c>
  <FilesMatch "^(index\.html|sw\.js|registerSW\.js|manifest\.webmanifest)$">
    Header set Cache-Control "no-cache, must-revalidate"
  </FilesMatch>
</IfModule>
